ferm (1.1.0.trunk.r433-1) experimental; urgency=low

  * Snapshot from upstream SVN r433. Needed packaging changes, so I went
    ahead and redid the packaging with cdbs.
  * Run ferm unit tests during build.
  * Provide an ifupdown pre-up hook that loads /etc/network/rules.ferm
    (Closes: #110928).
  * Upstream changes relevant to bugs:
    - Quoted comma-separated lists seem to work again (Closes: #241886).
    - The new "def $VAR = `shell-command`" syntax seems to fit this
      wishlist bug (Closes: #117730).
    - Undefined variable references cause errors now (Closes: #271965).
    - Support for multiport module (Closes: #252034).
    - Include command (Closes: #207505).
  * Bump standards-version to 3.6.1

 -- Tommi Virtanen <tv@debian.org>  Fri, 27 May 2005 11:50:01 +0300

